## CLAUDE.md — Corporate Bond Carry MVP

### Data Models
- `Bond`: CUSIP, issuer, coupon, maturity, OAS, duration, convexity, rating, sector
- `CarrySignal`: bond_id, date, gross_carry, net_carry (after funding), roll_down_component
- `Position`: bond_id, notional, entry_date, entry_price, current_mark
- `Trade`: bond_id, direction, notional, timestamp, execution_price, slippage

### Carry Calculation
Gross carry for bond i:
  carry_i = (yield_i - rf_funding) * duration_i + roll_down_i
  
Roll-down approximation:
  roll_down_i ≈ -duration_i * (yield(T-dt) - yield(T)) / dt

Net carry:
  net_carry_i = gross_carry_i - transaction_cost_i - financing_spread_i

### Storage
- Parquet files for historical data (date-partitioned)
- SQLite for position/trade state (MVP simplicity)
- No Postgres, no Redis (defer complexity)

### Boundaries
/src
  /data       → loaders, cleaners
  /signals    → carry calculation, other factors
  /portfolio  → optimization, risk
  /execution  → order generation, TCA
  /backtest   → simulation engine
/tests
/notebooks   → exploratory only, no production logic
